    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Humpty Doo &middot; Bees Creek &middot; Virginia &middot; Lambells Lagoon</span>
      <h1>Termite inspection in <span class="accent">Humpty Doo</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Humpty Doo is Litchfield Council acreage country, 40 minutes south-east
        of Darwin CBD on the Arnhem Highway. Most blocks here are 2&ndash;20Ha
        rural-residential with substantial bushland retained on the property and
        adjacent crown reserve. That&rsquo;s textbook Mastotermes darwiniensis
        territory &mdash; diffuse colonies, multi-hectare foraging range, and
        the world&rsquo;s most destructive termite chewing through any cellulose
        it can find.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
